In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2015 as National Family Caregivers Month. He acknowledges the important role that caregivers play in providing care and support to their loved ones. The President emphasizes the need for caregivers to have the necessary support and recognition for their selfless work. He highlights the efforts of his administration to improve the lives of older Americans and people with disabilities, including providing more options for aging in place and access to affordable health insurance through the Affordable Care Act. The President also expresses his commitment to making paid family leave available for all Americans and ensuring that veterans and their caregivers receive the benefits and care they deserve. He calls on Americans to honor and appreciate the contributions of caregivers and work towards a future where they receive the same support and understanding they show for those they care for.